Change log for duff
===================

Started as of version 0.3.1.

2006-01-07
 * duff.h: Added enum for symlink dereferencing modes.
 * duffentry.c: Fixed bug in get_entry_samples (credits to Alexander Bostrom).
 * duffdriver.c: Added recursion depth tracking.
 * duffdriver.c: Removed collection of symlinks to files.
 * duffdriver.c: Made stat_file aware of symlink dereferencing modes.
 * duff.c: Added -H option for following only symlinks listed as arguments.
 * duff.c: Reordered options for better clarity.

2006-01-04
 * duffentry.c: Removed code for -z option.
 * duffdriver.c: Do not collect empty files when using -z option.
 * duffdriver.c: Fixed unlink bug in report_clusters.
 * duffdriver.c: All entries are now freed by the cluster search phase.

2006-01-03
 * duff.h: Added inode and device fields to struct Entry.
 * duff.h: Added backlink to struct Entry.
 * duffentry.c: Added functions link_entry and unlink_entry.
 * duffentry.c: Added storing of device and inode fields.
 * duffdriver.c: Moved to using doubly-linked entries.
 * duff.c: Added -p option for physical mode (credits to Snow).
 * duffdriver.c: Implemented physical mode.

2005-12-14
 * duffdriver.c: Eliminated duplicate stat call for -L option.
 * duffdriver.c: Added inital sketch for symlink-aware -e option.

2005-12-01
 * duffutil.c: Fixed bug when printing off_t values on Mac OS X.
 * duffdriver.c: Added includes for building on Solaris.
 * duff.c: Added includes for building on Solaris.

2005-11-28
 * duff.1: Updated to reflect changes in the code.
 * duffdriver.c: Added primitive directory loop detection, with functions
                 has_recursed_directory and record_directory.
 * duffutil.c: Added hash function for device/inode pair.
 * duffdriver.c: Added several additional TODO items.
 * duff.h: Added struct Directory for recording of recursed directories.

2005-11-27
 * duffdriver.c: Added freeing of entries to report_clusters.
 * duffentry.c: Moved code for -z option into compare_entries.
 * duff.1: Updated to reflect changes in the code.
 * duff.c: Added file name reading from stdin.

2005-11-26
 * duff.c: Added -z option for ignoring empty files.
 * duff.c: Moved primary driver logic into duffdriver.c.
 * duffdriver.c: Created new file for primary driver logic.

2005-11-24
 * duff.c: Added missing 't' to the getopt string (credits to Richard Levitte).
 * duffentry.c: Fixed bug in ordering of comparison phases.

2005-11-23
 * duff.c: Fixed typo in help for -t option (credits to bitninja).

